---
import SiteLayout from '../../../components/SiteLayout.astro';

const title = 'What grip styles are there for a gaming mouse?';
const description =
  'Palm grip, claw grip or fingertip: the three grip styles determine which gaming mouse shape suits you. A quick guide to picking the right one for how you play.';

const fecha = 'June 12, 2026';
const dateISO = '2026-06-12';
const tiempoLectura = '4 min read';

const secciones = [
  { id: 'palm', label: 'Palm grip' },
  { id: 'claw', label: 'Claw grip' },
  { id: 'fingertip', label: 'Fingertip grip' },
  { id: 'cual-eres', label: 'Which grip is yours?' },
  { id: 'forma', label: 'Mouse shape by grip' },
  { id: 'recomendaciones', label: 'Recommended mice by grip' },
];
---

<SiteLayout title={`${title} | Monckey Gamer`} description={description} robots="index, follow" article={{ title, dateISO }}>
  <article class="post">
    <a class="category-back" href="/en/blog/">← Back to Blog</a>

    <header class="post-header">
      <span class="post-tag"><span class="post-tag-gg">GG</span> Gamer guide · Peripherals</span>
      <h1>What grip styles are there for a gaming mouse?</h1>
      <p class="post-lead">
        Not everyone holds the mouse the same way. Your grip style determines which mouse shape and size
        gives you more control and less fatigue. Knowing it completely changes how you choose.
      </p>
      <div class="post-meta">
        <span>{fecha}</span>
        <span class="post-meta-dot"></span>
        <span>{tiempoLectura}</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <nav class="post-toc" aria-label="Article contents">
      <span class="post-toc-title">In this article</span>
      <ul>
        {secciones.map((s) => (
          <li><a href={`#${s.id}`}>{s.label}</a></li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <div class="post-body">
      <section id="palm">
        <h2>Palm grip: your whole palm on the mouse</h2>
        <p>
          In the <strong>palm grip</strong>, your whole hand rests on the mouse:
          the palm sits on the back, the fingers extend relaxed over the buttons
          and the thumb and pinky hold the sides.
        </p>
        <ul class="post-list">
          <li><strong>Feel:</strong> relaxed, comfortable for long sessions, less fatigue.</li>
          <li><strong>Control:</strong> large movements from the elbow and shoulder. Less precision on micro-adjustments.</li>
          <li><strong>Ideal for:</strong> MOBA, RPG, low-sensitivity (low-DPI) FPS, general use.</li>
          <li><strong>Ideal mouse:</strong> large size (130mm+), raised shape at the back.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="claw">
        <h2>Claw grip: fingers arched like a claw</h2>
        <p>
          In the <strong>claw grip</strong>, the palm only touches the back
          of the mouse and the fingers bend into a "claw": the knuckles are raised and
          the fingertips are what press the buttons.
        </p>
        <ul class="post-list">
          <li><strong>Feel:</strong> more control and agility than palm. Takes some getting used to.</li>
          <li><strong>Control:</strong> a mix of wrist and arm movement. Very versatile.</li>
          <li><strong>Ideal for:</strong> competitive FPS, Battle Royale, any genre.</li>
          <li><strong>Ideal mouse:</strong> medium size (120–130mm), not too tall a profile.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Claw is the most common grip among competitive PC gamers. It offers precise
          control without sacrificing movement speed.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="fingertip">
        <h2>Fingertip grip: only the fingertips in control</h2>
        <p>
          In the <strong>fingertip grip</strong>, the palm does not touch the mouse at all.
          Only the fingertips are in contact with it. Movement comes exclusively
          from fingers and wrist.
        </p>
        <ul class="post-list">
          <li><strong>Feel:</strong> maximum agility and turning speed. Takes practice.</li>
          <li><strong>Control:</strong> fast, precise movements. Fatigues faster in long sessions.</li>
          <li><strong>Ideal for:</strong> high-sensitivity (high-DPI) FPS, precise flicking.</li>
          <li><strong>Ideal mouse:</strong> small size (110–120mm), low profile and low weight.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="cual-eres">
        <h2>How to find your natural grip</h2>
        <p>
          Place the mouse on the desk and grab it in a relaxed way without thinking about it.
          Look at where your palm rests:
        </p>
        <ul class="post-list">
          <li>Palm rests fully on the mouse → <strong>Palm grip</strong></li>
          <li>Palm touches the back, fingers bent → <strong>Claw grip</strong></li>
          <li>Palm does not touch the mouse, only fingers → <strong>Fingertip grip</strong></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Your hand size matters too. Measuring from wrist to middle finger:
          under 17cm = small hand; 17–19cm = medium hand; over 19cm = large hand.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="forma">
        <h2>Mouse shape based on your grip</h2>
        <div class="post-table-wrap">
          <table class="post-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Grip</th>
                <th>Ideal length</th>
                <th>Profile</th>
                <th>Weight</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Palm grip</td><td>125–145 mm</td><td>Tall and curved</td><td>Any (75–120g)</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Claw grip</td><td>120–130 mm</td><td>Medium</td><td>50–85g ideal</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Fingertip grip</td><td>110–120 mm</td><td>Low and compact</td><td>Under 65g ideal</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="recomendaciones">
        <h2>Recommended mice by grip type</h2>
        <ul class="post-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Palm grip — long sessions:</strong>
            <a href="/en/gaming-mice/razer-basilisk-v3-wired-26k-11buttons-3/">Razer Basilisk V3</a>
            — right-handed ergonomic, tall profile, very comfortable.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Claw grip — competitive:</strong>
            <a href="/en/gaming-mice/attack-shark-x3-wireless-paw3395-49g-1/">Attack Shark X3 49g</a>
            — medium ambidextrous shape, light, ideal for claw.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Fingertip grip — high-sensitivity FPS:</strong>
            <a href="/en/gaming-mice/pulsar-x3-crazylight-wireless-43g-white-2/">Pulsar X3 CrazyLight 43g</a>
            — the lightest in our catalog, compact shape for fingertip.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Claw / fingertip wireless with battery life:</strong>
            <a href="/en/gaming-mice/razer-basilisk-v3-x-hyperspeed-18k-285h-7/">Razer Basilisk V3 X HyperSpeed</a>
            — 285h of battery, ambidextrous claw/palm shape.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Every product page in our <a href="/en/gaming-mice/">gaming mice</a> catalog
          includes dimensions so you can check compatibility with your grip.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <aside class="post-cta">
      <h3>The right mouse for your grip</h3>
      <p>Find the ideal gaming mouse for palm, claw or fingertip in our catalog.</p>
      <a class="btn" href="/en/gaming-mice/">View gaming mice</a>
    </aside>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>

<style>
  .post { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .post-header { margin: 18px 0 32px; }
  .post-tag { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 7px; font-size: 0.68rem; font-weight: 500; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.14em; color: #8aa0b8; }
  .post-tag-gg { font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: 0.05em; color: #7cffcb; border: 1px solid rgba(124,255,203,0.3); border-radius: 5px; padding: 1px 5px; font-size: 0.62rem; }
  .post-header h1 { margin: 18px 0 16px; font-size: clamp(1.6rem,6vw,2.8rem); line-height: 1.15; overflow-wrap: break-word; }
  .post-lead { margin: 0 0 18px; color: #c8d8e8; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .post-meta { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; color: #8aa0b8; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .post-meta-dot { width: 4px; height: 4px; border-radius: 50%; background: #8aa0b8; }
  .post-toc { margin: 0 0 40px; padding: 24px 28px; border-radius: 20px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
  .post-toc-title { display: block; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: #7cffcb; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .post-toc ul { margin: 0; padding: 0; list-style: none; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2,minmax(0,1fr)); gap: 10px 24px; }
  .post-toc a { color: #c8d8e8; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; transition: color 0.2s ease; }
  .post-toc a:hover { color: #7cffcb; }
  .post-body section { margin-bottom: 40px; scroll-margin-top: 24px; }
  .post-body h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; color: #e6f7ff; margin: 0 0 16px; padding-left: 14px; border-left: 3px solid #7cffcb; }
  .post-body p { color: #c8d8e8; line-height: 1.8; margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .post-body strong { color: #e6f7ff; }
  .post-body a { color: #7cffcb; text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  .post-list { margin: 0 0 16px; padding: 0; list-style: none; display: grid; gap: 12px; }
  .post-list li { color: #c8d8e8; line-height: 1.7; padding-left: 26px; position: relative; }
  .post-list li::before { content: ""; position: absolute; left: 4px; top: 11px; width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; background: #7cffcb; }
  .post-table-wrap { margin: 0 0 18px; overflow-x: auto; border-radius: 16px; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
  .post-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .post-table th { text-align: left; padding: 14px 20px; color: #7cffcb; font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
  .post-table td { padding: 13px 20px; color: #c8d8e8; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05); }
  .post-table tbody tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .post-table td:first-child { color: #e6f7ff; font-weight: 500; }
  .post-cta { margin-top: 48px; padding: 36px; border-radius: 24px; text-align: center; background: linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(0,255,225,0.06),rgba(27,183,255,0.06)); border: 1px solid rgba(124,255,203,0.15); }
  .post-cta h3 { margin: 0 0 8px; font-size: 1.4rem; color: #e6f7ff; }
  .post-cta p { margin: 0 0 20px; color: #c8d8e8; }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .post-toc { padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 28px; }
    .post-toc ul { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .post-lead { font-size: 1rem; }
    .post-meta { flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
    .post-body section { margin-bottom: 32px; }
    .post-body h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; }
    .post-table { font-size: 0.85rem; }
    .post-table th { padding: 11px 12px; font-size: 0.7rem; }
    .post-table td { padding: 10px 12px; }
    .post-cta { padding: 28px 20px; }
    .post-cta h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; }
    .post-cta .btn { width: 100%; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 380px) {
    .post-table th, .post-table td { padding: 9px 10px; font-size: 0.8rem; }
  }
</style>
